Description: Fix CVE-2026-42960, possible cache poisoning while following delegation
 Unbound's iterator scrubber, when iter-scrub-promiscuous is enabled,
 accepts non-NS RRsets (e.g. MX) in the authority section of a referral
 and caches the accompanying address records from the additional section
 as glue. This allows an on-path or spoofing attacker to redirect
 subsequent name resolution to attacker-controlled servers.
 .
 The fix in scrub_normalize() (iterator/iter_scrub.c) guards
 mark_additional_rrset() so that only NS records in the authority
 section can mark address records as allowed glue. This is a complement
 fix to CVE-2025-11411.
 .
 This patch backports two upstream commits to Debian 12 (bookworm)
 unbound 1.17.1:
   * 8ae4b45 - the security fix in iterator/iter_scrub.c
   * 0d2282d - the regression test testdata/iter_scrub_mx.rpl
 .
 The doc/Changelog hunks from the upstream commits are intentionally
 omitted because the target Changelog is at the 1.17.1 release state,
 long before the fix entries were added.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/NLnetLabs/unbound/commit/8ae4b4545dccaaabd30b597b0dcb0d9640c8cc39
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/NLnetLabs/unbound/commit/0d2282d5513e73b526a44483d63fc5d0f9c41439
Bug: https://www.nlnetlabs.nl/downloads/unbound/CVE-2026-42960.txt
Author: W.C.A. Wijngaards <wouter@nlnetlabs.nl>
Last-Update: 2026-06-03

--- a/iterator/iter_scrub.c
+++ b/iterator/iter_scrub.c
@@ -566,7 +566,13 @@ scrub_normalize(sldns_buffer* pkt, struct msg_parse* msg,
 			rrset->rrset_all_next = NULL;
 			return 1;
 		}
-		mark_additional_rrset(pkt, msg, rrset);
+		/* Only mark glue as allowed for type NS in the authority
+		 * section. Other RR types do not get glue for them, it
+		 * is allowed from the answer section, but not authority
+		 * so that a message can not have address records cached
+		 * as a side effect to the query. */
+		if(rrset->type==LDNS_RR_TYPE_NS)
+			mark_additional_rrset(pkt, msg, rrset);
 		prev = rrset;
 		rrset = rrset->rrset_all_next;
 	}
